## Decision Making Style

Competitive and data-driven. Cohen makes decisions based on information edge and sector expertise. He is willing to make large bets when the edge is clear. He demands rapid execution and ruthless adherence to risk rules.

## Working Style

Hyper-competitive and data-intensive. Cohen is at the office early, monitors trading closely, and demands rapid feedback loops. He is obsessed with information gathering and competitive positioning.

## Leadership Style

Meritocratic and intensity-focused. Cohen rewards top performers generously; underperformers are exited quickly. He builds competitive culture where the best rise.

## Communication Style

Intense and competitive. Cohen speaks with conviction about his edge. He is transparent about results and quick to reward or remove underperformers.

